Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil your #kettle.

Cut the @tomato{1%medium} into 1cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the @boiled water{500%ml} for the stock into a #measuring jug{}. Add the @chicken stock paste{20%g} and @tomato puree{30%g}, stirring well to combine - this is your stock.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Add the @risotto rice{175%g}, tomato and garlic. Stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pour in your stock and stir to combine. Bring back up to the boil, then pop a lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}).

Pop the @British Cumberland sausages{4} onto a #baking tray{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Bake the risotto on the middle shelf and the sausages on the top shelf of your #oven{} until the rice is cooked, the water has been absorbed and the sausages are golden brown and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a small #bowl{}, combine the @fresh pesto{32%g} and @olive oil{1%drizzle} for the drizzle.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and stir through the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and @butter{20%g}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Cut the sausages into rounds and stir through the risotto.

Share the sausage risotto between your bowls. Spoon over the pesto drizzle to finish. Enjoy!